race.comment: CAMILLA (5) found one better in tougher in Canberra on a slow surface but there was plenty of merit in the weather. The Snowden-trained mare deserves to break through and draws well with Heywood a positive jockey engagement. Hard fit and is worth another chance. MILLY MOLLY MANDY (2) can improve third-up. Her provincial form before the spell stacks up for this and has an inside gate and the blinkers on again. The 3kg claim brings her right into it. COOL AS POPEYE (6) raced favourite at Canberra first-up but didn't get into it (vet cleared). She has the ability but gives away big starts. Fitter and is likely to be finishing hard. Keep a close eye on the betting with SATIN AND CASH (8), who needed the Canberra run on debut. Has a key jockey switch to McDougall, who strikes at 30% with the yard.
